### Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080

### ============================
### End-to-end scenario
### Run these in order
### ============================

### Step 1 — Register Alice near the pickup point
POST {{baseUrl}}/drivers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice",
  "location": {
    "latitude": 1.0,
    "longitude": 1.0
  }
}

###

### Step 2 — Register Bob further away
POST {{baseUrl}}/drivers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bob",
  "location": {
    "latitude": 10.0,
    "longitude": 10.0
  }
}

###

### Step 3 — Check nearby drivers — Alice should appear first
GET {{baseUrl}}/drivers/nearby?latitude=0&longitude=0&count=2

###

### Step 4 — Request a ride — Alice should be allocated (nearest)
POST {{baseUrl}}/rides
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "pickupLocation": {
    "latitude": 0.0,
    "longitude": 0.0
  }
}

###

### Step 5 — Check nearby again — Alice should be GONE (BUSY)
GET {{baseUrl}}/drivers/nearby?latitude=0&longitude=0&count=2

###

### Step 6 — Request another ride — Bob should be allocated
POST {{baseUrl}}/rides
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "pickupLocation": {
    "latitude": 0.0,
    "longitude": 0.0
  }
}

###

### Step 7 — All drivers busy — expect 503
POST {{baseUrl}}/rides
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "pickupLocation": {
    "latitude": 0.0,
    "longitude": 0.0
  }
}

###

### Step 8 — Complete Alice's ride (replace with real ride ID from Step 4)
### Alice should become AVAILABLE, completedAt should be set
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/rides/{{aliceRideId}}/complete

###

### Step 9 — Alice is back — should reappear in nearby
GET {{baseUrl}}/drivers/nearby?latitude=0&longitude=0&count=2

###

### Step 10 — Complete same ride again → expect 409
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/rides/{{aliceRideId}}/complete
